To make the tuna filling, mix the marinade ingredients together in a bowl, add the tuna and set aside for 10 minutes.Heat a little olive oil in a frying pan over a medium heat and fry the tuna for 3-5 minutes until just cooked. Add the tuna to the marinade and mix well to combine.To make the sauce, blend the ingredients together in a food processor and season with salt and pepper.To assemble, brush the tortillas with a little olive oil, sprinkle over the cheese and toast under a hot grill until melted. Top with the tuna and soured cream sauce and serve.